I wish to drift,
Off into sleep, 
To arrive at the next day, 
Sooner. 

But wanting to sleep, 
Makes me toss and turn, 
Frustrated I'm not asleep, 
Sooner. 

If only I calmed, 
My rush, my need, 
I'd get there a lot, 
Sooner.

#poetrycommunity

I want to sit,
Next to the glow of a campfire.
I want to play melodies,
That fill the black.

I want to be a little orange light,
To compete with the yellow ones above.
I want my song to join,
The stories in the sky.

I want my story to matter.

To be rid of questions, 
That weigh down a heart.
